                    <span>I've been deployed in Iraq for the last year and I've read a lot of books for lack of anything better to do and this one stands out. I've never really been able to relate to a novel written by a female before but this was easy. I was laughing out loud and finding myself very anxious to read on til the very end. Fans of Palahniuk and Bret Easton Ellis would throughly enjot this novel.</span>
                  
              
